The paper discusses security challenges and solutions in the context of blockchain-enabled Internet of Vehicles (IoV), which involves data sharing among vehicles. This topic falls under the intersection of computer security (cs.CR) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The proposed solution involves reputation-based voting and contract theory, which are related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper uses numerical results to evaluate the proposed solution, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG).
